             China may make the China Investment
Corp. sell off its banking stakes so it can meet requirements to
invest in the U.S., the Financial Times reported, citing
unidentified people familiar with the matter.  
 Under the proposals, the $200 billion sovereign wealth fund
will no longer be responsible for holding the governmentâ€™s
